FBIS4-60118 "drnes099dd_94012" FBIS-NES-94-099 Daily Report 22 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Fatah Hawks `Terrorists' Join Security Forces Fatah Hawks `Terrorists' Join Security Forces TA2205142094 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR in Hebrew 22 May 94 p 2 TA2205142094 Tel Aviv 'AL HAMISHMAR Hebrew BFN [Report by ITIM] [Text] Seventy Fatah Hawks terrorists were recruited to the Palestinian security forces in the Gaza Strip yesterday. Of the 70 -- who constitute the total number of Fatah's terrorists and fugitives -- some 30 will be incorporated into the Palestinian police force; approximately 20 will join the security service under Muhammad Dahlan's command, while the rest will join the military force, or will renounce this privilege and become civilians. A senior Israeli source said the Israeli security forces were unaware of this agreement.
